This paper is about improving the performance of Neural Machine Translation (NMT) on new and potentially unknown domains. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes papers on natural language processing and machine translation. The paper also discusses adaptive ensemble weighting, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper mentions L2 and Elastic Weight Consolidation, which are regularization techniques commonly used in machine learning, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category. The paper also discusses extending Bayesian Interpolation with source information, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
